title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 14 §§ 635-12.11 - Effect on liability and entitlements
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 14 §§ 635-12.11 - Effect on liability and entitlements

State Regulations
(a) This section applies to all services, whether or not they are preexisting services. (b) Nothing in this Subpart shall be
construed as a release of any liability for services, whether they were
delivered before, on or after the payment start date. (c) Any reduction or waiver of a fee shall
not constitute nor be construed as a release of the individual or any liable
party from liability for payment of the full fee. (d) Nothing in this Subpart shall be deemed
to create any entitlement to services. Notes
